An ideal probe source has high shot-to-shot stability. This would result in a modulation of the probe purely from the excitation of the sample. However, the observed signal includes fluctuations of the laser condition and background noise from the camera. A good measure for the similarity of the individual shots is given by the Pearson product moment correlation coefficient31. The correlation coefficient is calculated according to2γλ,j=∑i=1n-j(Eλ,i-E¯λ)(Eλ,i+j-E¯λ)∑i=1n-j(Eλ,i-E¯λ)2∑i=1n-j(Eλ,i+j-E¯λ)2,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
